 * sha256(geometry) on the witnessed isub bus) is exposed as a SELF-DESCRIBING quantum carrying its eidos -- its
 * content-address (identity), its verb (purpose), and a CAPABILITY TAG (1 bit: ORDER for a BELOW block,
 * COMPLEMENT/involution for a REFLECT block -- the universal operation the geometry realizes).
 *
 * ENCAPSULATE, NOT REIMPLEMENT (the cardinal law, [[feedback_one_substrate_no_islands]]): the capability web
 * already exists -- assimilate builds it via recognise-and-merge (assim_add), fed in production by the
 * pipeline_real trace spine (xii_rewrite -> unravel -> ingest -> assim_add).  descriptor is a THIN FOLD over
 * assimilate's exports: it does NOT rebuild the web, it DESCRIBES it and BRIDGES it to the Composer.
 * desc_build_order folds the web's BELOW order into eidos::compose quanta, so the planner routes GOAL-DIRECTED
 * over the web (the descriptors are DERIVED from the blocks, never hand-tagged).
 *
 * HONEST SCOPE (calibrated): corpus 1940 proves descriptor faithfully folds a web built via the REAL primitive
 * (assim_add); the END-TO-END trace feed (a real execution shattered onto the bus) is NOT exercised there --
 * that is the production source.  So "trace-derived input" is the design, PROVEN only when a real trace drives
 * the bus.  CAVEAT: desc_count == the CURRENT isub bus contents (== "the assimilate web" only when the bus holds
 * only the web).  And descriptor does NOT create a live CONSUMER of EIDOS's planning (that remains tp_*).
 * "descriptor done" != "EIDOS is live" and != "trace-feed proven end-to-end".
